<TITLE> Manindra Lal suspended </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)  The government has suspended Khagrachhari District Council chairman Manindra Lal Tripura, CHT affairs ministry said in a statement on Sunday. "Manindra Lal was suspended as he had been arrested in a murder case. His suspension order will be effective from Oct. 31," Mohammad Abu Hashim, executive officer of the Khagrachhari District Council confirmed to bdnews24.com. He said he had received the statement signed by senior assistant secretary Nazma Khanom in the afternoon. Monindra secured bail in the case on Nov. 16 from Khagrachhari district judge Mohammad Mostofa Ahmed on a bond of Tk 30,000. Police detained him on Oct. 31 in Dhaka and showed him arrested on charges of murdering Anupam Tripura. He was sent to Dhaka Central Jail. Five other accused in the case have been detained in Khagrachhari District Jail. bdn
